title: 820-3437 Green/Orange light no boot after Wine spill
message:
Got this board today, trying to figure out whats wrong with it.
I have gone through all the S5 rails and their all present.

The board is completely dead and [FONT=Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif][SIZE=2][COLOR=#333333]PM_SLP_S5_L, PM_SLP_S4_L and PM_SLP_S3_L are all missing.[/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]

[FONT=Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif][SIZE=2][COLOR=#333333]​I'm assuming this is because the PCH is not getting power, but what powers the PCH?

Help much [/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT][FONT=Verdana, Arial, Tahoma, Calibri, Geneva, sans-serif][SIZE=2][COLOR=#333333]apprechiated :)[/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]

title: 820-3437 Green/Orange light no boot after Wine spill
message: Check RTC resistors R1300, R1301, R1302 and R1303, should have about 3.3V on each pin, also check if PCH_CLK32K_RTCX1 is present.....

message:
